00%20US%20dollars)%20a%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhaving-kids-two-decades-apart-taught-learned-life-lessons-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edecided%20to%20have%20children%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20we%20thought%20we'd%20do%20what%20all%20our%20friends%20were%20doing.%20Most%20families%20in%20our%20circle%20had%20two%20parents%20with%20corporate%20jobs%20and%20a%20nanny.%20We%20tried%20that%20at%20first%2C%20but%20when%20I%20came%20home%20and%20realized%20my%20son%20had%20more%20of%20the%20nanny's%20mannerisms%20than%20mine%20or%20my%20husband's%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20a%20different%20option.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221cfe5d63-8b02-446f-9708-6cfc437ea126%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20became%20a%20millionaire%20by%20focusing%20on%20being%20debt-free%20by%2040%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20was%2032%2C%20I%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-you-should-know-before-starting-a-small-business-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estarted%20my%20business%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20At%20first%2C%20the%20business%20was%20a%20financial%20drain%3A%20I%20had%20not%20only%20lost%20my%20corporate%20income%2C%20but%20I%20was%20pouring%20money%20into%20the%20business.%20I%20felt%20financially%20dependent%20on%20my%20husband.%20We%20had%20always%20agreed%20to%20keep%20finances%20separate%2C%20and%20I%20had%20to%20ask%20him%20for%20money%20to%20get%20my%20hair%20done.%20It%20was%20quite%20humiliating%2C%20to%20be%20honest.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20the%20while%2C%20I%20had%20a%20goal%3A%20be%20debt-free%20by%2040.%20When%20I%20told%20my%20husband%20this%2C%20he%20laughed.%20We%20had%20just%20bought%20a%20home%20in%20Sydney%2C%20where%20the%20real%20estate%20prices%20rival%20New%20York%20City.%20Paying%20that%20off%20seemed%2C%20well%2C%20laughable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELuckily%2C%20my%20business%20did%20well.%20It%20grew%20slowly%20over%20time%2C%20but%20then%2C%20in%202021%20had%20a%20big%20leap%20after%20I%20found%20a%20great%20mentor.%20The%20business%20started%20having%20%24100%2C000%20AUD%20(about%20%2465%2C000%20USD)%20months%20and%20never%20went%20back.%20Just%20before%20my%2040th%20birthday%20we%20paid%20off%20our%20primary%20residence%2C%20the%20last%20of%20our%20debt.%20I%20was%20a%20millionaire.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22767d4ab8-306a-4817-913b-ac8bc7a41720%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20kids%20are%20enrolled%20in%20an%20entrepreneurship%20school%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20I'm%2042.%20Money%20and%20time%20are%20never%20problems%20for%20me.%20In%20the%20corporate%20world%2C%20I%20made%20%24250%2C000%20AUD%2C%20working%20about%2050%20hours%20a%20week.%20I%20have%20more%20cash%20flow%20and%20work%20about%2022%20hours%20a%20week.%20My%20lifestyle%20is%20completely%20different%2C%20and%20I'm%20able%20to%20be%20there%20more%20for%20my%20kids.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat's%20the%20promise%20of%20entrepreneurship.%20Both%20my%20kids%2C%20who%20are%2012%20and%2010%2C%20are%20enrolled%20in%20a%20business%20school%20for%20kids%20that%20teaches%20them%20about%20founding%20companies.%20They%20spend%20about%2090%20minutes%20each%20weekend%20studying%20business%2C%20and%20it%20has%20a%20real%20impact%20on%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERecently%2C%20my%2012-year-old%20made%20%2430%20from%20his%20babysitting%20business.%20He%20was%20excited%20about%20the%20money%20and%20also%20about%20how%20much%20fun%20he%20had.%20That%20is%20the%20dream%3A%20to%20be%20paid%20really%20well%20for%20something%20that%20gives%20other%20people%20value%20and%20that%20you%20enjoy.%20I%20want%20my%20kids%20to%20think%20differently%20about%20how%20they%20can%20achieve%20that.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ef35bde8-0ad3-4b2c-a96b-d1da50464474%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI'm%20teaching%20the%20kids%20to%20save%20and%20invest%2C%20even%20when%20I%20want%20to%20buy%20them%20things%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20neither%20my%20husband%20nor%20I%20grew%20up%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20money%2C%20it's%20really%20important%20to%20us%20that%20our%20kids%20know%20how%20to%20manage%20money%20and%20grow%20wealth.%20We%20don't%20want%20them%20just%20waiting%20on%20an%20inheritance%2C%20which%20we%20see%20from%20some%20friends%20who%20have%20generational%20wealth.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe're%20teaching%20them%2C%20starting%20with%20allowances%20and%20gifts.%20All%20monetary%20gifts%20from%20birthdays%20or%20Christmas%20are%20put%20into%20a%20savings%20account%2C%20and%20we're%20now%20teaching%20the%20kids%20about%20investing%20that%20money.%20They%20also%20get%20%2420%20a%20month%20for%20completing%20basic%20chores%20like%20taking%20out%20the%20trash.%20They%20can%20use%20that%20money%20for%20impulse%20buys%20like%20candy%20or%20save%20it%2C%20which%20my%20son%20recently%20did%20for%20a%20new%20Nintendo%20game.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESometimes%2C%20I%20just%20want%20to%20buy%20them%20candy%20or%20games.%20I%20stop%20myself%20because%20letting%20them%20understand%20the%20value%20of%20their%20money%20is%20an%20important%20lesson.%20Hopefully%2C%20it%20will%20keep%20them%20from%20being%20financially%20dependent%20on%20me%20and%20allow%20them%20to%20grow%20their%20wealth%20long%20term.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdropped-out-of-high-school-still-became-a-millionaire-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733743681000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673f55c6ede4eeae3928c7ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdropped